FRONTEND CORRECTION — form_submit payload location
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

When user clicks Submit on the MRR form, the request body must keep
the SAME shape as a regular chat message (module_name, message,
thread_id). The form_submit object goes inside the "message" field
as a JSON STRING.

Currently being posted (WRONG):
{
  "module_name": "MRR",
  "action": "form_submit",       <-- these should NOT be at top level
  "form_id": "mrr_create_form",
  "data": { ... },
  "thread_id": "..."
}

Should be posted (CORRECT):
{
  "module_name": "MRR",
  "message": "{\"action\":\"form_submit\",\"form_id\":\"mrr_create_form\",\"data\":{...}}",
  "thread_id": "..."
}

Where the value of "message" is JSON.stringify(formSubmitObject).

In JavaScript:
    const formSubmit = {
        action: "form_submit",
        form_id: "mrr_create_form",
        data: { project_id, requisition_type, need_by_date, comments, items }
    };
    const body = {
        module_name: "MRR",
        message: JSON.stringify(formSubmit),
        thread_id: currentThreadId
    };

Backend will detect the JSON-string message starts with the
form_submit action and route it accordingly (similar to how Excel
upload routes by uploaded_files presence).

Cancel button: post as before with module_name + message: "cancel"
+ thread_id. (Just a plain text message.)

